## Decision Points & Edge Cases

**What if a founder arrives without a completed Quarter Map?**
Sprint Planning renders with a dependency gate. The board is visible but non-interactive. A notice directs them to complete the Quarter Map first. The Sprint Goal screen is not accessible.

**What if a founder has a saved draft but no locked Quarter Map?**
Draft is preserved but uneditable until the Quarter Map dependency is resolved.

**What if a founder tries to lock without all nine capabilities having initiatives?**
The "Lock My Sprint →" button is disabled. The progress indicator shows exactly which capabilities are missing initiatives. Each incomplete capability card has a visible indicator.

**What if a founder wants to edit the sprint goal after locking it?**
The sprint goal can be unlocked and re-edited before the sprint is locked. Once the sprint itself is locked, the goal cannot be changed without creating a new sprint version. This preserves historical integrity.

**What if a founder wants to add more than two Prioritize initiatives per capability?**
Soft guardrail — a notice surfaces. They can override. The platform does not hard-block. The choice is theirs — the platform just makes the consequence visible.

**What if the Plant or Iterate volume guardrail is triggered?**
Same pattern — soft notice, not a hard block. The founder can override with intention.

